                   |___/                                                            

-First you need to put your login, socks password in the config.yml file.
-For kerberos authentication, you need to put your unix password in the config.yml 
 and build NsToken ruby/c extension in lib/kerberos directory.(ruby extconf.rb && make)
-You can run the script like this : "ruby rubysoul-server.rb" or "./rubysoul-server.rb"

[Commands options]
  --help, -help, -h, -H : Print this help message.

*************************************************
* RubySoul-Server V0.7.03                       *
* Christian KAKESA <christian.kakesa@gmail.com> *
* kakesa_c - ETNA_2008                          *
*************************************************

---

[Example of "config.yml"]
#--- | Application config
:login: kakesa_c
:socks_password: 'my_socks_password'
:unix_password: #--- | Only if you have build lib/kerberos/NsToken, if you don't must be empty.
:user_group: ETNA_2008
:system: Ubuntu Jaunty Jackalope
:location: @Home
:log_dir: '/var/log'
...

